<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="891" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/886: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Costa Rican Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Venegas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                        1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.45
                                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>I have the honor to inform Your Excellency that my Government, on the
                                strength of the Constitution of 1871 now in force, has decreed that
                                the elections of the President of the Republic and deputies to the
                                National Congress be held on the first of December next.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Venegas</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>